<br>
We had every damn Hibernian keep last night for HOURS! Hibs didnt even show up. We could have taken the Str Relics easy last night, but we didnt even attempt it. We just wanted to farm RPs. Hibs called us on it.. they didnt even come out... basically said &quot;Hey come take our relics.&quot; But Mids didnt. Obviously because they dont want to give up the CS. Thats just pathetic. <br>
<br>
Im on the fence about this. I see the good and bad about it. What are your thoughts on the CS? <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#A89378><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub141.ezboard.com/beverquestpeople.showUserPublicProfile?gid=snowleeper>Snowleeper</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Almost an Addict</span><br>  Posts: 97<br> <font color=#BBBFC5>(1/27/03 3:34:34 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub141.ezboard.com/feverquestpeoplefrm46.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=51.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: DAoC: Corpse Summoner....</span><hr size=1> Allowing CSing inside an enemy realm will eventually destroy the game.  The only  thing that prevents zergs is the travel time invovled in daoc.<br>
<br>
Add to that people are using the cs to come right back and die w/o rps while earning more rps.<br>
<!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://vnboards.ign.com/message.asp?topic=44125719&amp;replies=39" target="top">From VNboards</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--><br>
