<br>
We were moving into Albion for an eventual relic raid, and got beat on at the Hadrian's/Penine border by a huge Albion force. Instead of that buying the Albs some time, we all transferred to our CS and Eras, and they had been leapfrogged. Do they try to intercept us moving out of Eras, leaving the border open? Do they split their force?<br>
<br>
It might encourage more frontier play,  which would be good, but it might appeal to a lower common denominator than I want to see in the game. I like that taking relics is difficult and time consuming. I'm not sure i want it watered down. <p><!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>Gallatin</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
